## 🧩 Model abstraction

Cryptol definitions with no real-code counterpart (placeholders, uninterpreted functions, ABI adapters). The notes column explains what each one stands in for.

| Function | Source | Maps to | Notes |
|----------|--------|---------|-------|
| [`canonLenPrefixed`](functions/canonLenPrefixed.md) | model (SDEP) | — | Bounded fixed-width encoder used only for length-prefix reasoning. The general string canonicalizer in `cpp/src/canonical.cpp` is unverified. |
| [`hmacSha256`](functions/hmacSha256.md) | model (SDEP) | — | Algebraic placeholder; NOT SHA-256. Real HMAC is implemented in `cpp/src/hmac.cpp` and remains unverified. |
| [`isValidSignature`](functions/isValidSignature.md) | model (SDEP) | — | Constant-time comparison contract; the production constant-time-equals helper is unverified. |

## Excluded helpers

2 functions excluded from the matrix via `coverage.toml [exclude].functions` (not security-relevant): `to_lower`, `trim`.
